comments: Simmons (BKN) continues to move laterally into White (CHI) after the initial contact during the screen, affecting his ability to defend over the pick.
Thomas (BKN) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Simmons (BKN) makes incidental contact with Vucevic's (CHI) arm after he tips the ball towards the basket.
As O'Neale (BKN) gains possession of the rebound, marginal contact occurs as Vucevic's (CHI) hand slides off of O'Neale's arm.
LaVine (CHI) is moving alongside Bridges' (BKN) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
O'Neale (BKN) establishes himself in Caruso's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

As Vucevic (CHI) establishes post position, he reaches backwards and contact occurs with O'Neale's (BKN) head.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
O'Neale (BKN) legally contests the driving shot attempt by LaVine (CHI) and absorbs the ensuing contact.
Thomas's (BKN) shot attempt does not make contact with the rim and the shot clock expires.
Bridges (BKN) legally contests the driving shot attempt by LaVine (CHI) and avoids making contact.
Officials stop play due to a shot clock malfunction and the Bulls retain possession upon the resumption of play.
O'Neale (BKN) jumps vertically and absorbs the ensuing contact with LaVine (CHI) during his driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) commits a take foul on Bridges (BKN).
Simmons (BKN) commits a take foul on Lavine (CHI) and the illegal contact occurs prior to the start of his shooting motion.
